On this exercise you MUST have a main like this:

int	main(int argc, char **argv)
{
	t_student	a;

	if (argc != 4)
		printf("invalid input\n");
	[...]
	printf("Name: %s\n\n", a.name);
	printf("Math grade: %f\n", a.math);
	prinf("Portuguese grade: %f\n\n", a.portuguese);
	printf("Average: %f", a.average);
}

you're only allowed to change one line, the one with [...] to a function call.
